{
  "text": "Liver tissues were fixed in 10% (v/v) phosphate buffer formalin and embedded in paraffin wax. The paraffin sections (4-6 \u00b5m thick) were segmented, and each was stained using hematoxylin and eosin stain and examined under an optical microscope (Olympus DP70, Olympus Optical Co., Tokyo, Japan) integrated with a camera [CITATION_1] .",
